name: Half-Price Mid-Day Open Play
description:
**Half-Price Mid-Day Open Play for All Levels**

\
Come play at half-price to de-stress in the middle of your day! All levels are welcome and the session will be hosted by one of our coaches.

\
**Players who sign up for Open Play are expected to know the rules of pickleball. If you are new to pickleball, please attend an Intro to Pickleball Clinic before coming to an Open Play event.**

\
**Max players per court: 6**

\
**Cancellation Policy:** Full refund until 24 hours before the session starts. Cancellations within 24 hours will be subject to a full charge.

\
**Low Enrollment Cancellation**: We will cancel sessions that do not have a sufficient number of players by 8pm the prior evening.  You will not be charged and will receive a notice of the cancellation via email.

name: Clinic - Intro to Pickleball
description:
**Introduction to Pickleball**

\
This Intro to Pickleball Clinic will cover the rules and basic principles of Pickleball, such as scoring, serving, return of serve, court positioning, dinking, and volleying. The final half hour of the clinic will be used to play supervised games.

\
Our clinics are based on a curriculum developed by the [Racket Professional Organization](https://racketpro.org/) (RPO), founded by Collin Johns, who many consider to be one of the world's best pickleball coaches. Our excellent team of coaches has been trained in the RPO method, and we think you will find it to be game-changing in terms of the quality of instruction.

\
**There will be a 4 to 1 player to coach ratio (or less) for this clinic.**

\
**Cancellation Policy:** Full refund until 24 hours before the session starts. Cancellations within 24 hours will be subject to a full charge.

\
**Low Enrollment Cancellation**: Clinic will run even if only a single person has signed up, so no need to worry about cancellations!

name: Gotham Women's Collective
description:
**Gotham Women’s Collective** \n 

A weekly space to grow your game and build community—on and off the court. This isn’t just another clinic. It’s not a drop-in drill session or private lesson. \n 

The Gotham Women’s Collective is a weekly gathering for women of all levels to train with purpose, play with intention, and grow through a culture of support. Each session blends competitive fun with real coaching and community energy. Players will rotate through skill-building drills, partner play, and game-based learning—guided by rotating Gotham coaches and special guest players dedicated to uplifting and empowering women on the court. Expect: \n 

* Weekly themed training (reset, attack, movement, etc.)
* Game strategy + real-time coaching
* Matchplay with feedback
* Optional fixed partner opportunities

  \

Whether you're new to the game or looking to refine your competitive edge, this space is built for you—and for all of us. All levels welcome. All women-supported identities embraced.

\
Let’s rally. Let’s learn. Let’s grow—together.

\
**Players who sign up for the Women’s Collective are expected to know the rules of pickleball (e.g., how to keep score, 2 bounce rule, etc.). If you are new to pickleball, please attend an Intro to Pickleball Clinic before coming to a Women’s Collective event.**

\
**Max players per court: 5**

\

name: Clinic Series - Path to 4.0 Level 1
description:
**Clinic Series (6 classes) - Path to 4.0 Level 1**

\
This clinic series is designed for players who currently play at an Intermediate capability and are seeking the skills to progress to the 4.0 level. Each class in the series will focus on one of the 6 key elements of the **RPO 201 program**: Dinking, Volleys, the 3rd Shot Drop, Serving, Driving, and Groundstroke. The final half hour of the class will transition to supervised games so that participants have an opportunity to apply the skills in a competitive scenario.

\
Our clinics are based on a curriculum developed by the [Racket Professional Organization](https://racketpro.org/) (RPO), founded by Collin Johns, who many consider to be one of the world's best pickleball coaches. Our excellent team of coaches has been trained in the RPO method, and we think you will find it to be game-changing in terms of the quality of instruction.

\
**Max per class: 4**

\
**Cancellation policy:** Because of the challenge of finding a last minute replacement for a clinic series, cancellations must be made at least 3 days prior to the start of the first session.

\
**Cancellation for low enrollment:** The clinic series will be cancelled for low enrollment if it does not have at least 3 registered participants prior to the first class.

name: Coached Open Play with Alex Lanson and Adam Walsh
description:
**Morning Coached Open Play with Alex and Adam**

\
**Note: Coach Kayla will be substituting for Coach Alex during this session**

\
**Start your day with intentional reps and smart play.** \n 

This isn’t your average open play — it’s a **coach-guided, feedback-rich session**

designed to help you grow your game while having fun. \n 

**What to Expect:** \n 

* 2 hours of structured match play across multiple courts
* Grouped by level for competitive and balanced games
* Coach-led rotation system to ensure fresh matchups
* Personalized tips and in-game feedback
* Time for questions, breakdowns, and strategy advice

name: Clinic - DUPR Assessment Workshop with Coach Van
description:
**Clinic - DUPR Assessment Workshop with Coach Van**

\
**Max number of players: 6**

\
This is a special clinic for players who who do not yet have a DUPR rating and wish to receive a provisional rating from a certified [DUPR coach](https://www.duprcoach.com/coach-cert).

\
During this session, you will spend 2 hours playing in a round robin format using traditional scoring. Coach Van will be assessing your skills and strategic approach to the game throughout the entire session.

\
After the clinic has concluded, Van will document your performance. Assuming you do not already have a rating, you will be assigned a provisional DUPR rating within the DUPR app. You will receive an email from Coach Van with the details of the assessment.

\
Prior to coming to the session, please download the My DUPR Coach App using [Coach’s Van’s unique link](https://n7r4j.app.link/UxjI7frimOb?_p=c91229c09b007af2e1038cffec).
